practiceConfig.specificIssue: Section 498A - Cruelty by Husband or Relatives of Husband
practiceConfig.caseSummary: The case involves a married woman who alleges physical and mental abuse by her husband and in-laws over a period of two years. She has filed a complaint under Section 498A IPC. The defense claims the allegations are exaggerated and driven by property disputes. The case will examine evidence of cruelty, witness credibility, and medical reports.
practiceConfig.opponentStrengths: Strong in legal precedents, skilled in witness discrediting, adept at technicalities in procedural law.
practiceConfig.keyArguments:
- Establishing a consistent pattern of abuse with evidence
- Refuting the "false allegation" defense
- Citing past judgments that upheld conviction under Section 498A
- Responding to procedural objections
